                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4288.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-24T16:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1912—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am officially informed that the Mexican Government will do its utmost to
                    capture Ciuad Juárez without a battle, by starving it out if necessary, if the
                    American Government will help by stopping entry of supplies. Unless otherwise
                    instructed, I shall make no reply to this note.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
